snippet.textDisplay:
SPOILERS FOR THE GAME





The Nameless Puppet is Carlo's dead corpse, which Geppetto turned into a puppet to later revive his son. In order to do so he needed a tremendous amount of Ergo, the Arm of God, and Carlo's Ergo which he forcefully attempts to remove from you at the end of the game.

The main character of the game, P, is a puppet crafted to be the temporary vessel for Carlo's Ergo(which is Carlo's distilled memories and soul). Nearly everything that occurs in the game is apart of Geppetto's plan to revive his dead son. The one thing that Geppetto didn't account for is the temporary vessel having it's  Ego awaken(If you managed to gain enough humanity by the end of the game.), and by extension becoming Carlo himself. Geppetto, however, refuses this fact. Still wholeheartedly believing that the hollow shell that was once his son, is still Carlo.

The final battle of the game is quite literally a battle between the body and the soul of Carlo. One being, two separate entities.

(It's been awhile since I completed the game so I am a bit rusty on the lore, just fyi.)
